flow diagrams~
The flow diagrams are painted directly onto the walls in precise administrative drafting, their lines and labels showing the complete reclaim processing chain. The "Intake" stage references civic remainder classification: bodies unclaimed within fourteen days of interment are automatically reclassified as institutional property. The "Classification" stage assigns each set of remains a labor category: hauling, guard service, excavation, or "specialized disposition." The "Assignment" stage matches classified remains to requisition orders from other departments. The "Deployment" stage records the activation of reclaim rites and the transfer of reanimated labor to its assigned post. The entire system is documented with the meticulous care of a municipal works department processing building materials.
