#5234
Inner Archive~
The Matriarch's personal archive, a small chamber containing the records she kept separate from all institutional filing systems. @@mLead-lined cabinets@@N hold documents in the Matriarch's own hand: private correspondence, personal observations on the behavior of bound dead, experimental notes on the limits of reclaim-rite binding, and most disturbingly, a personal registry of individuals she considered particularly valuable as reclaim stock, annotated with notes on their skills, knowledge, and potential utility. The archive reveals the Matriarch not as an administrator but as a collector, someone who viewed the dead as resources to be catalogued and deployed.
