#5235
@@mMatriarch's @@pThrone Sanctum@@N~
The innermost sanctum of the Nightveil Matriarch is a chamber of concentrated authority whose every surface radiates with the full power of the @@mblood-memory binding system@@N. A personal @@marchive-throne@@N of smaller scale than the dais in the main sepulcher chamber occupies the center, its surface inscribed with the Matriarch's personal binding formula rather than the institutional text of the outer dais. @@pSealed Name tablets@@N are arranged on shelves within arm's reach of the throne, allowing the Matriarch to consult and manipulate individual identities without leaving her seat of power. The chamber is suffused with a @@msteady magenta glow@@N that emanates from the binding inscriptions themselves, casting no shadows. The air is utterly still and carries the taste of old iron and preserved ceremonial oils. This is where the Nightveil Matriarch, Keeper of Sealed Names, held absolute dominion over the dead and their memories.
~
