#5236
@@mAuditor's @@pChamber@@N~
Beyond the Matriarch's sanctum lies the domain of the Sepulcher Lich, the Last Auditor of the Dead, the entity that embodied the ultimate fusion of bureaucratic authority and necromantic power. This chamber was the Auditor's workspace and seat of judgment, where the final accounting of the dead was performed. A massive @@maudit lectern@@N dominates the center, its surface covered in the binding formulas that allowed the Auditor to assess, catalogue, and reclaim any identity within the Nightfall system. The walls bear the complete @@pmaster registry@@N of every individual who ever passed through the catacombs, living or dead, willing or coerced. The @@mmagenta glow@@N here is at its most intense, the binding energy so concentrated that the air itself seems to vibrate. The Auditor's domain represents the final evolution of Nightfall's institutional corruption: the moment when the bureaucracy of death became fully autonomous, no longer serving the city but serving only its own perpetuation.
~
