@@pSepulcher @@mTerminus@@N~
The sepulcher levels end at a final threshold where the Matriarch's institutional architecture gives way to the older, humbler stonework of the exit passages. A single @@Winscription@@N marks the boundary, carved in a hand different from any of the institutional scripts found elsewhere in the complex: "What was done here was done in the name of the city. The city must decide whether the name was honestly given." The inscription's authorship is uncertain, but its placement at the boundary between the Matriarch's domain and the exit passages gives it the quality of a challenge directed at the world above.
