inscription~
The inscription is carved in a steady, unhurried hand that bears no resemblance to the administrative scripts, military notation, or necro-liturgical formulas found elsewhere in the catacombs. It may be the work of one of the dissenters, placed here as a final statement at the boundary of the Matriarch's power. Or it may be older, a message from the original Nightfall chapel builders who constructed this passage before the institution consumed the chapel tradition entirely. The ambiguity is itself a kind of message: the question of responsibility, like the question of ownership over the dead, remains unresolved.
