#5240
@@dExit @@pPassages@@N~
The passage opens into the beginning of the exit corridor network, a series of chambers designed to provide egress from the deepest levels of the catacomb complex. The architecture here is deliberately neutral, stripped of the institutional symbolism that saturates every other level of Nightfall. The walls are plain stone, the corridors are wide enough for comfortable passage, and the air carries a freshness that suggests proximity to surface ventilation shafts. The contrast with the oppressive authority of the sepulcher levels is startling and clearly intentional: whatever conclusion the Matriarch's system reached, these passages offer a physical return to the unmarked, uncommanded world. An @@arootglass testimony wall@@N occupies the east face of the entry chamber, its crystalline surface containing the final readable lore of the Nightfall complex.
~
