rootglass testimony wall~
The rootglass wall is the largest single rootglass formation in the catacomb complex, its surface a mosaic of captured voices and preserved memories that span the entire history of Nightfall. The voices speak in layers: Midgaard civic notation mixed with forest oath formulas, institutional pronouncements overlaid with personal grief, administrative language punctuated by whispered protests. The wall does not resolve these contradictions or offer a unified narrative. Instead, it presents the full, unedited record of what Nightfall was: a civic institution that became a predator, a burial system that consumed its own purpose, and a place where two incompatible traditions of memory were forced together and ultimately both betrayed.
~
