#5241
Memorial Approach~
A corridor leads south toward the memorial chamber, its walls bearing simple carved names without the elaborate institutional formatting found elsewhere in the catacombs. These are not registry entries but personal memorials, names left by those who passed through the exit corridors and felt compelled to leave a mark of their own choosing. The @@Wnames@@N are carved in dozens of different hands, spanning what appears to be a long period of time, evidence that many people passed through these corridors and chose to remember on their own terms.
~
