@@aMemorial @@GChamber@@N~
The final chamber of the Catacombs of Nightfall is a memorial space whose design draws on both Midgaard civic tradition and Great Northern Forest burial custom. A single @@arootglass testimony wall@@N occupies the south face, its crystalline surface containing the clearest captured voices anywhere in the complex, speaking in measured alternation between civic record-keeping cadence and forest oath formulas. An @@Wascending passage@@N leads up toward the surface gateworks, providing a shortcut return to the upper levels. The chamber's @@Winscription@@N reads: "The systems of Nightfall are interrupted but not cleansed. The records remain. The forest's memory continues to resist. The city's debt to the unnamed is unpaid." The @@aluminescence@@N of the rootglass fills the chamber with a steady @@Ggreen-gold light@@N that feels like the first honest illumination in the entire complex, neither institutional authority nor necromantic power but simply the forest's patient, persistent memory refusing to be erased.
~
